				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes, you can update the CPU's copy of OAM outside of vblank. In fact, you're supposed to.
<br />
<br />VRAM is any RAM mapped into PPU $0000-$2FFF. It includes CIRAM, the memory inside the NES used for nametables, and CHR RAM, the memory inside the cartridge used for pattern tables. Some cartridges have CHR ROM instead of CHR RAM; for these, the only VRAM is CIRAM.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

